### 2. Handling Item Stacking

To handle item stacking, you can modify the `Item` class to keep track of the quantity. Here's a revised code snippet:

```python
init python:
    class Item(object):
        def __init__(self, name, description):
            self.name = name
            self.description = description
            self.quantity = 1

        def increase_quantity(self, amount):
            self.quantity += amount

        def decrease_quantity(self, amount):
            self.quantity -= amount

        def is_empty(self):
            return self.quantity <= 0

    class Inventory(object):
        def __init__(self):
            self.items = {}

        def add_item(self, item):
            if item.name in self.items:
                self.items[item.name].increase_quantity(1)
            else:
                self.items[item.name] = item

        def remove_item(self, item):
            if item.name in self.items:
                self.items[item.name].decrease_quantity(1)
                if self.items[item.name].is_empty():
                    del self.items[item.name]
```

